gurmukhi: hxY dust pustM mhw ssqR DwrM ]
transliteration: Hanai Doust Poustan Mahaa Sastra Dhaaran||
translation: He killed prominent tyrants with his sharp-edged weapons.
He conquered many enemies like Lord Rama, the killer of Ranana.28.196.
One day the King Janmeja went hunting.

gurmukhi: lKy miRg DwieE gXo Aaur dysM ]
transliteration: Lakhe Mrig Dhaaio Gado Aur Desan||
translation: Seeing a deer, he pursued him and went to another country.

gurmukhi: sRimE prm bwtM qikE eyk qwlM ]
transliteration: Sramio Param Baatan Takio Ek Taalan||
translation: After the long and arduous journey, the king was tired; when he saw a tank,

gurmukhi: qhwN dauV kY pIn pwnM auqwlM ]29]197]
transliteration: Tahaan Daud Kai Peen Paanan Outaalan||29||197||
translation: He ran there quickly to drink water.29.197.

gurmukhi: kirE rwj sYnM kiFE bwr bwjM ]
transliteration: Kario Raaj Sainan Kadhio Baar Baajan||
translation: Then the king went to sleep. (the destiny) caused a horse to come out of water.
He saw the beautiful royal mare.

gurmukhi: lgXo Awn qw ko rhXo qwih grBM ]
transliteration: Lagyo Aan Taa Ko Rahyo Taah(i) Gadabhan||
translation: He copulated with her and made her pregnant.

gurmukhi: BieE isAwm krxM su bwjI AdrbM ]30]198]
translation: From her an invaluable horse of black ears was born.30.198.
The king Janmeja began his great horse-sacrifice.

gurmukhi: ijxy srb BUpM sry srb kwjw ]
transliteration: Jine Sarab Bhoopan Dare Sarab Kaajaa||
translation: He conquered all the kings and all his errands were set right.

gurmukhi: gfXo j`g QMBM krXo hom kuMfM ]
transliteration: Gadyo Jagg Thanbhan Daryo Hom Koundan||
translation: The columns of the sacrificial place were fixed and the sacrificial altar was constructed.

gurmukhi: BlI BwNq poKy blI ibpR JuMfM ]31]199]
translation: He satisfied nicely the assembly of the Brahmins giving wealth in charity.31.199.
